      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(slack): fail unconfirmed threaded deliveries",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nSlack threaded payload delivery could still be reported as successful when Slack did not actually confirm the requested origin thread. The previous guard checked `result.threadTs`, but `sendMessageSlack` may preserve the requested `opts.threadTs` as a compatibility fallback in the public result and receipt. That meant an unconfirmed threaded send could look confirmed to the outbound adapter.\n\nThis PR is related to #96692, but it is scoped to the fail-closed confirmation contract for threaded Slack payload sends.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nThe adapter needs a value that only comes from Slack's API response, not from OpenClaw's requested send options. This patch adds `confirmedThreadTs` to `SlackSendResult` only when Slack returns `message.thread_ts`, keeps the existing `threadTs`/receipt behavior for compatibility, and makes the outbound adapter validate threaded payload delivery against `confirmedThreadTs`.\n\nThat separates \"requested or canonical thread id for callers\" from \"Slack confirmed this specific thread in the response\", which is the distinction needed for the fail-closed guard.\n\n## User Impact\nThreaded Slack block/payload sends now fail clearly when Slack returns a message without confirming the requested thread, or when Slack confirms a different thread. Confirmed threaded sends still succeed and include the normal Slack result fields.\n\nThis avoids silently treating generated-but-not-confirmed threaded completions as delivered in the expected Slack thread.\n\n## Evidence\nHead commit: `a5877d86b5d3c249f0b8e1ac6e929139b53b0d4f`.\n\nLocal targeted behavior proof:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/slack/src/outbound-adapter.test.ts extensions/slack/src/send.blocks.test.ts` -> 2 files passed, 36 tests passed.\n- `pnpm oxfmt --check extensions/slack/src/send.ts extensions/slack/src/outbound-adapter.ts extensions/slack/src/outbound-adapter.test.ts extensions/slack/src/send.blocks.test.ts` -> all 4 touched files formatted.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test` -> passed.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions` -> passed.\n- `git diff --check` -> no whitespace errors.\n\nBehavior cases covered by the tests:\n\n- `sendMessageSlack` leaves `confirmedThreadTs` unset when Slack only returns a message id and OpenClaw only has the requested `threadTs` fallback.\n- `sendMessageSlack` sets `confirmedThreadTs` when Slack returns canonical `message.thread_ts` for text, chunked, and block sends.\n- `slackOutbound.sendPayload` rejects threaded payload delivery when the result only echoes the requested `threadTs` without `confirmedThreadTs`.\n- `slackOutbound.sendPayload` rejects a different confirmed Slack thread and accepts the matching confirmed thread.",
        "branch": "fix/slack-thread-delivery-confirmation",
